{{!--
    HTML template for One-Time-Password email
    =========================================

    Available params:

      {{originName}}: The name of the origin (e.g. "myapp.company.com")

      {{otp}}: The OTP code

      {{otpId}}: The OTP ID. Can be used to generate magic links to your app. App can use db.cloud.login({email, otpId, otp}), reading these params from query.

      {{isApp}}: True if the OTP is to be entered in an app, false if it's to be entered on a web site.

      {{email}}: The email address of the receiving user.

--}}
Your OTP for {{originName}}: <strong>{{otp}}</strong><br /><br />
<b><u>WARNING</u></b><br/>
{{#if isApp}}
  This OTP must only be entered on <b><u>{{originName}}</u></b> and never on a web site.
{{else}}
  This OTP must only be entered on <b><u>{{originName}}</u></b> and never on any other site. Check the address bar before entering it.
{{/if}}
